@aiwalter I think it is an interesting concept and I'm generally supportive of it. But what's a concrete use case? 

The example (which I know is just for illustrative purposes), adds a scaled version of the input data exeogenous data (minmaxscalar), it doesn't seem like that would add value in AutoArima (since I believe it is performing regression with ARIMA error structure when there is exogenous data). 

Would be good to have a specific example that could be used to give an idea of good use cases.
